<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-13T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="379" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2981: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-13T20:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">March 13,
                                        1919, 8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    March 13, 4.35 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Serious fracas occurred between American soldiers, Japanese policemen,
                            and civilians Tientsin yesterday, to-day. Full report not yet <pb facs="0506" n="421" xml:id="pg_421"/> received. Have sent First
                            Secretary of Legation, Japanese Minister has [sent] his [secretary], to
                            confer with the consuls Tientsin.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>